Modular rewrite of MeleeEnv
- Modularized agents: it is now fairly straightforward to write an agent
and pass it into the environment. Agents handle their own act methods
and store their controllers. There are now much fewer controller references floating
around. These were confusing and hard to work around.

- Modularized action and observation spaces: MeleeEnv is now independent
of the action and observation spaces, so space implementations/designs
can be compared for performance. Action spaces keep track of what
actions are available but also designate how actions are carried out.
Observation spaces determine what information goes to the agent.

- The old random agent was rewritten to be more modular. New agents
include human, cpu, and shine agents. See `ai/agents/basic.py` for more.

New features, improvements
- All agents now consume observations and the action space so that the
game knows when they have been defeated via `is_defeated`.
- Agents store `self_observation`. This is inserted instead of [-1, -1,
-1, -1...] into the observation when agents are defeated. The previous
design was problematic for agents who utilized position. The new method
preserves the agent's final state, which should proivide indication
about whether that opponent is still targetable.
